114.9	Authoritarianism	Authoritarianism	Authoritarianism is a form of social organization characterized by submission to authority. It is usually opposed to individualism and libertarianism. In politics, an authoritarian government is one in which political authority is concentrated in a small group of politicians.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Engelbert_Dollfuss.png/170px-Engelbert_Dollfuss.png
